<TITLE> Faruk stresses Pak apology for 1971 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gopalganj, Apr 10 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh will continue to have a psychological distance with Pakistan as long as the country does not apologise for the genocide it carried out in 1971 during the Liberation War. Commerce Minister Faruk Khan also said on Saturday that diplomatic relations with Pakistan would not improve either. Speaking at the playground of Muksudpur S J High School in Gopalganj, he said that during the war, Pakistan army committed murders, rapes, loot and arson in Bangladesh as instructed by its political leaders and Yahia Khan. "Pakistan must apologise for the brutal killings in 1971." Regarding the trial of war criminals, the minister said, "War criminals have been punished in different countries of the world." But he said that Bangladesh was yet to do so. "We have already started the process." Faruk Khan said that the trial process was being fully transparent to the entire world and in conformity with the international standards. bdn
